args:
After recovering the mimicries from the lab,
Sandalphon reveals the truth behind them,
the Empyrean War, and the Sigils. Afterward,
everyone sets to work gathering the angels'
mana and bringing them back to life.
These are the mimicries the Archdemons\nwere sealed inside! Will these really let\nus revive the angels?
Yes. Now let us split up and transport\nthem aboveground.
Demonic entities keep pouring in from\nthe sewers! Are there any other exits?
Only one: a set of stairs leading into\nChurch Headquarters and from there\nout to the city center.
That's great, except that they're\nALSO on the stairs!
We saw the demonic entities pouring in\nand came running.
What's going on here, Pinon?\nHow is Sandalphon alive?
I ask that explanations be postponed.\nSecuring the mimicries so we might revive\nthe Five Archangels must take priority.
In that case, we'll handle the bad guys.\nThe rest of you take those bodies\nand make for the evacuation site.
(The whole time I ran with her body\non my back, my heart was pounding.)
(I carried the weight of my lost hope\nthere in my arms.)
The Deck of the Gran Fiore
The evacuees are nearly all boarded.\nAlso, I'm informed the prince has returned\nwith a surviving angel.
Yes, and we're about to debrief the new\narrival. Apparently, there's talk of a way\nto bring the deceased angels back.
There may just be hope yet...
Just seeing Sandalphon alive was enough\nto blow my mind, but now you're saying\nwe can bring the other angels back?
Indeed. And with the Halidom's assistance,\nthe probability of success rises. I would\nespecially welcome the Auspex's aid.
I will do all that I am able.
So how do these mimicries fit in?
These artificial bodies are copies of\nangels, created to seal demons within.

But prolonged exposure to miasma led the
souls instilled in them to merge with the
demons, and these combined souls were
lost when the demons were freed.
Interesting that the bodies didn't vanish\nonce they lost their souls like the real\nones did.

A consequence of their artificial nature.
At present, they are devoid of souls,
but their life-support functionality is still
fully operational.
Sounds like they exist in something akin to\na coma. And if the Archangels' souls are\nintact and not returned to mana...
Then those souls should be able to take\nroot in the mimicries, resulting in the\nArchangels' revival.
Dude, that's AWESOME! But, um,\nis it really possible to do all that?
Finlorda himself proved you can house\na soul within such a vessel.
And if that vessel is a near-identical copy\nof the soul's original body, I think the\nchance of success will be even higher.
So we can really get Gabriel\nand the others back?!
Before we move on under the assumption\nthat such a thing is possible, I have a\nquestion for Sandalphon.
Michael was unaware of any demons\nsealed within bodies copied from the\nangels until Loki told him of it.
In fact, none of the angels even possessed\nmemories of themselves having been\ncopied. Yet you know all about it. Why?
As much as I wish to believe you,\nI cannot trust you until I understand\nwhat's really happening here.
A sensible protest. Then before we\nproceed, I will explain how I possess\nknowledge of the mimicries.
When I asked about them before, you told\nme you were unable to reply—not that you\nhad no knowledge of it.

And now I am able to offer that reply.
I will tell you all I can of the mimicries,
the Empyrean War, and the truth behind
the Sigils.
When Satan first appeared a thousand years ago,\nmy elder sister, Metatron, fought back his\nonslaught and sealed his soul in another world.

His flesh remained here, divided into parts and
scattered across the land. In time, those pieces
became a demonic army lead by the Five
Archdemons.
Metatron rallied the angels and, along with the\nChurch, began to slay the demons—and so began\nthe Empyrean War some 700 years ago.

In time, they reached a stalemate. The human and
angelic forces were exhausted, so Metatron sought
to end the war by sealing away the Archdemons.
For with their leaders gone, the rest of the demon
host would be easily put to route.

Her plan was to create copies of the angels: the
mimicries. She chose five angels capable of
serving as vessels, trapped the Archdemons within
their copies, then locked them away in another
world. A double prison, meant to last forever.

The sealing stones were the linchpins holding that
prison shut, and they were given to the Church.
For as dragons were given to individual
idiosyncrasies, it was thought an organization
would prove a more steadfast steward.
Just as Metatron planned, the demon forces fell\nonce their leaders were lost, and the conflict came\nto an end. But alas, a problem soon arose.
The Church asked Metatron to share the\ntechnology used to create the mimicries\nin case the Archdemons ever returned.
So they could seal 'em away again even\nif the angels weren't there to help, right?\nWhere's the problem with that?

The power is not limited merely to angels.
It could, for example, be used to copy
dragons and shape their will, just as the
original five were made to accept exile.
If people were to use such a power to\ncreate an army of obedient dragons,\nwhat would be the result?
Regardless, the dragons would not abide it.\nAt worst, it could spark another war\nbetween people and dragonkind.
But Metatron could not ask the Church to\nguard the sealing stones, then deny them\noutright. So she proposed an alternative.

The Five Archangels would be ceded to the Church.
In exchange for their might, the Church would ask
no further about the means to create mimicries.
The mutual bonding of lives we know as the Sigils
were a means of enforcing this bargain.

Metatron then had all record of the mimicries
purged from the Church so none might seek out
the means of their creation in the future. This is
why records of the Empyrean War are so few.

The angels' vague memories of the war's events
and their ignorance of the mimicries was another
of Metatron's interventions. She modified their
memory so as to prevent the spread of potentially
catastrophic knowledge.
So Gabriel and the others were handed\nto the Church as a...a bargaining chip?
The angels agreed to their new mission\nand the memory modification. They went\ninto it with their eyes fully open.
Even so, it feels like they were treated\nlittle better than mere tools.
Your story accounts for why the Archangels\nwere with the Church, but what of you?
I came under Metatron's orders so I might\nkeep watch over the Church and ensure\nthat any sensitive information stay buried.
As such, my memories remain intact.\nHowever, Metatron took other measures\nto ensure I could not divulge any secrets.
A spell preventing me from communicating\nthe information I just shared. Should I try,\nI would immediately lose consciousness.
Which is why you were ＂unable to answer＂\nthe question previously.
I get that it's an important secret to keep,\nbut what kind of lady messes around with\nher little sister's noodle?
All that said, she configured the\nrestriction spell to lift automatically \nunder one specific condition...
The neutralization of all Five Archangels.\nMy sister thought the information might\nbe necessary in furnishing replacements.
This is why she enabled me to share it\nonly during such an event.
And what would happen if you died before\nthem? All knowledge of mimicries and the\nEmpyrean War would simply be lost?
Should I and four of the Archangels die,\nthe seal upon the last remaining angel's\nmemories would be broken.

Even to prevent a war, suppressing vital
intel to the very end is a poor strategy.
We could have used what you knew to
battle the demons.
Metatron believed the apostles and angels\nwere quite capable of defeating the Five\nArchdemons without that knowledge.
In point of fact, you lacked knowledge\nof the mimicries, yet still succeeded\nin neutralizing the Archdemons.
So what about Satan? Metatron didn't\nthink to leave behind any information\nabout him with the Church?
Her reasons for suppressing that were\ntwofold. First, the battle with Satan\npredated the Church's foundation.
As such, the Church was unaware of both\nhis existence and how the other demons\nwere born of his fragments.
If they knew that a threat greater than the\nArchdemons existed, they would have\ndemanded a force equal in power.
So she kept knowledge of Satan hidden\nin order to prevent them from amassing\npower beyond their means.

Secondly, the seal binding Satan was
thought to be unbreakable—and as such,
she saw no need to pass on knowledge
of him.
I'm all for having confidence in your work,\nbut that's ridiculous. Did she have a reason\nto think her seal would last forever?
Satan's seal is a special bond breakable\nonly with Metatron's own power. Naturally,\nshe had no intention of ever doing so.
Barring some critical mistake on her part,\nSatan's revival was a literal impossibility.
She thought that, even in the event of her\ndeath, her Shard would be protected for\neternity by the Sacred Tree.
When she passed away, her soul and\npower indeed became a Shard at the\nSacred Tree.
But when the Sacred Tree fell, the Shard\npassed into Loki's hands.
The destruction of the Sacred Tree was a\ntragedy unforeseen by Metatron or myself.
As for Metatron, she disappeared shortly\nafter the Empyrean War's end.

She was my sister, and I always believed
she was out there somewhere, alive and
happy. It...it never occurred to me that she
might actually have passed.

My explanation has grown long, but this
is the reason I have extensive knowledge
of the mimicries. Furthermore, I was
involved in their creation as well.
As such, I can state the following as fact:\nResurrecting the angels is possible.
Though I was unable to speak, I understand\nthat my erstwhile silence may undermine\nyour trust in me. But please—help me.
How many missions have we survived\nbecause we trusted your orders?
Nothing's changed. Just tell us what to do,\nand we'll bring the others back.
Hey, when the lady's right, she's right.\nWhat's the order, boss?
Harken now. The operation to restore the\nArchangels will commence as follows...
